  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies a design-space coordinate for a single variation axis, pairing an axis tag with a value.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate` binds a variation axis (identified by its
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate.Axis> tag) to a specific
design-space <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate.Value>. Use a span of
these coordinates with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments.VariationDesignPosition> or
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(System.ReadOnlySpan{SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate})>
to position the font on its variation design space.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var coord = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate
{
    Axis = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'g', 'h', 't'), // weight axis
    Value = 700f,
};
using var bold = typeface.Clone(new[] { coord });
```
]]></format></remarks>
